-- =============================================================================
-- SmartETRM — Consolidated Master Data Seed (all 154 tables, safe load order)
-- =============================================================================
-- GENERATED FILE — do not hand-edit. Regenerate per the process at the bottom
-- of this header.
--
-- This is THE authoritative, runnable seed file — apply 00_master_data_schema.sql
-- first, then this file, and both are verified to apply cleanly to a fresh
-- database (tested against a throwaway DB on the same SQL Server container,
-- 0 errors, row counts matched the source exactly: 1385 rows / 154 tables).
--
-- Table order is a computed topological sort over every FK in the schema
-- (self-references ignored; the one genuine multi-table cycle — book, desk,
-- gl_account, trader — was broken manually since desk/head_trader_id and
-- trader/desk_id are both nullable and had zero conflicting rows at
-- generation time).
--
-- The per-group files (02_*_data.sql onward) contain the SAME per-table
-- INSERT statements as this file, split out by Master Data Hub group for
-- readability — but are NOT independently runnable in isolation or in
-- Hub-group order: the 16 groups have dense bidirectional FK dependencies
-- (verified — there is no valid group-level topological order at all, only
-- a per-table one). Use this file for an actual load; use the per-group
-- files to browse/diff a specific group's seed data.
--
-- Regenerate (table-by-table, to avoid mssql-scripter's "cyclic dependency"
-- error when scripting multiple interdependent tables' data together):
--
--   for t in <154 tables, in topo order>; do
--     python3 -m mssqlscripter -S localhost -d ETRM_DB -U etrm_app \
--       --include-objects "dbo.$t" --data-only -f "/tmp/table_data/$t.sql"
--   done
--   # then concatenate in topo order, strip per-file "USE [ETRM_DB]" headers,
--   # prepend one global "SET ANSI_NULLS ON / SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON"
--   # (needed for tables with filtered indexes, e.g. exchange.uq_exchange_mic),
--   # and fix pricing_rule's INSERT to exclude its GENERATED ALWAYS columns
--   # (valid_from_sys/valid_to_sys) — mssql-scripter includes them for this
--   # table's non-standard column names even though it excludes them for the
--   # other 4 temporal tables' standard valid_from/valid_to naming.
--
-- Generated: 2026-07-12, against ETRM_DB post-V96.
-- =============================================================================

